Spicy Cabbage Soup (Weight Loss)
  --Breana Lai Killeen, M.P.H., RD

2 tbsp evoo
2 c chopped onions 
1 c chopped carrot
1 c chopped celery
1 c chopped poblano or green bell pepper
4 large cloves garlic, minced
8 c sliced cabbage
1 tbsp tomato paste
1 tbsp minced chipotle chiles in adobo sauce
1 tsp ground cumin
1/2 tsp ground coriander
4 c low-sodium vegetable broth or chicken broth
4 c water
2x15 oz cans low-sodium pinto or black beans, rinsed
3/4 tsp salt
1/2 c chopped fresh cilantro + more for serving
2 tbsp lime juice 
crumbled queso fresco, nonfat plain Greek yogurt and/or diced avocado for garnish

Heat oil in a large soup pot (8 qt or larger) over medium heat. Add onions, carrot, celery, poblano (or bell pepper) and garlic; cook, stirring frequently, until softened, 10-12 min. Add cabbage; cook, stirring occasionally until slightly softened, ~10 min more. Add tomato paste, chipotle, cumin and coriander; cook, stirring, for 1 min more. Add broth, water, beans and salt. Cover and bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce heat and simmer, partially covered, until the vegetables are tender, ~10 min. Remove from heat and stir in cilantro and lime juice. Serve garnished with cheese, yogurt and/or avocado, if desired. 


Notes: pick non starchy veggies to add

Serving Size: 1 1/2 cups
Per Serving: 167 calories; protein 6.5g; carbohydrates 27.1g; dietary fiber 8.7g; sugars 6.6g; fat 3.8g; saturated fat 0.6g; vitamin a iu 2968.9IU; vitamin c 47.2mg; folate 48.4mcg; calcium 115mg; iron 2.3mg; magnesium 50.5mg; potassium 623.7mg; sodium 408.1mg; thiamin 0.1mg. 
